</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-49_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The implementation of teletriage systems has significantly improved the efficiency of patient assessment in emergency departments. Teletriage services provide remote consultations and initial assessments, increasing accessibility and reducing wait times.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-51_ pf-heading-1-h3">Portable diagnostic devices</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-53_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The adoption of portable diagnostic devices has enhanced the speed and accuracy of diagnoses in urgent care settings. These devices provide immediate test results, allowing for quicker decision-making and treatment initiation.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-jIkXHa bGnPis pf-55_ pf-heading-1-h3">Automated dispatch systems
</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-57_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Automated dispatch systems have improved the coordination and response times of emergency medical services. These systems streamline communication and resource allocation, ensuring timely assistance to patients in need.
